to the editor your june 15 editorial the next big antitrust case questionably concludes that the justice department would serve the public 's interests if it prevailed in its suit against mastercard and visa you accuse the two bank associations of failing to innovate because of the cozy relationship between the banks that make up the mastercard and visa associations but mastercard competes vigorously with visa for the allegiance of banks and for consumer loyalty competition between the associations and their banks is precisely what led to the proliferation of cards allowing consumers to earn airline miles and contribute to charities and other innovations the government asserts that its remedy would benefit consumers american express and the discover card but it 's clear that american express alone is the government 's de facto client noah j hanft senior vice president mastercard international washington june 16 2000

